concept_explanation.mocking_chat_client:
**Mocking ChatClient in Spring AI tests:**

```java
// Test configuration that provides a mock ChatClient:
@TestConfiguration
static class MockAiConfig {
    @Bean
    @Primary
    ChatClient.Builder mockChatClientBuilder() {
        // Create mock chain:
        ChatClient mockClient = mock(ChatClient.class);
        ChatClient.ChatClientRequest mockRequest = mock(ChatClient.ChatClientRequest.class);
        ChatClient.CallResponseSpec mockCallSpec = mock(ChatClient.CallResponseSpec.class);
        ChatClient.ChatClientRequestSpec mockSpec = mock(ChatClient.ChatClientRequestSpec.class);

        when(mockClient.prompt()).thenReturn(mockRequest);
        when(mockRequest.user(anyString())).thenReturn(mockSpec);
        when(mockSpec.call()).thenReturn(mockCallSpec);
        when(mockCallSpec.content()).thenReturn(
            '{"category": "FRAUD", "confidence": 92, "requiresHuman": true}');

        ChatClient.Builder builder = mock(ChatClient.Builder.class);
        when(builder.defaultSystem(any())).thenReturn(builder);
        when(builder.build()).thenReturn(mockClient);
        return builder;
    }
}

// Simpler alternative: WireMock for Anthropic API:
@WireMockTest(httpPort = 8089)
class AiContractTest {
    @Test void stubAnthropicResponse() {
        stubFor(post(urlEqualTo("/v1/messages"))
            .willReturn(aResponse()
                .withStatus(200)
                .withHeader("Content-Type", "application/json")
                .withBodyFile("anthropic-fraud-response.json")));
        // Test with real HTTP client pointing to WireMock port
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.deterministic_testing:
**Deterministic AI tests with temperature=0:**

```java
// application-test.yml:
spring:
  ai:
    anthropic:
      chat:
        options:
          temperature: 0.0  # deterministic output
          seed: 42          # same seed = same output (model-dependent)

// Test: same prompt → same structured output
@Test void classification_isDeterministic() {
    // With temperature=0, same input always produces same output
    String result1 = classifier.classify("payment failed declined");
    String result2 = classifier.classify("payment failed declined");
    assertEquals(result1, result2); // deterministic!
}
```

